Ingredients:

Dough:
2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
1 1/2 teaspoons kosher salt
1 tablespoon light brown sugar
2 1/4 teaspoons instant yeast
1 cup warm water
Filling:
2 slices Black Forest deli ham, finely diced
1 cup shredded Gruyere cheese
Baking soda wash:
1 cup hot beer
1/4 cup baking soda
Egg wash:
1 large egg
Everything seasoning salt
2 tablespoons melted butter

Steps:

1. In the bowl of a stand mixer with the dough hook attached, add flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Stir to combine. Add the water and knead the dough for 5 to 6 minutes, until soft and smooth. Add dough to a lightly greased bowl and cover with a towel. Place in a warm place for 1 hour, until doubled in size.

2. While dough is resting, make the filling by combining the ham and cheese in a small bowl.

3. Beat 1 large egg in another small bowl. In a third bowl, whisk together the hot beer and baking soda.

4. Heat oven to 400 degrees, and line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. Spray with nonstick spray.

5. Lightly grease your work surface. Use a rolling pin to roll dough into a 12x14-inch rectangle. Cut the dough lengthwise into 4 strips. Roll each strip out with a rolling pin until it’s roughly 4 inches wide. Lay the strip out so the long side faces you. Brush the top of the strip with egg wash. Sprinkle one-fourth of the filling on the bottom third of the strip. Roll the strip up into a long rope and pinch the edges to seal. Roll to smooth. Turn the dough rope into a U-shape then twist the ends twice. Press the dough down where it overlaps.

6. Dip each pretzel into the beer mixture. Place on the sheet tray, brush with egg wash and sprinkle with everything seasoning.

7. Bake pretzels for 15 minutes, until golden brown. Remove from oven and drizzle with butter. Enjoy warm.

node.title: Get a little knotty by making fresh ham & cheese stuffed pretzels. 🥨

#ad For a banana split sundae you can enjoy on any occasion, turn to this next-level version by @chefgraceramirez. Soaked berries, carmelized & flambéed bananas and a few scoops of your favorite @lactaid ice cream flavors come together to make a lactose-free treat that has all of the taste and none of the discomfort. 

Ingredients:

3 tablespoons of grapeseed oil
6 ripe bananas, peeled and sliced in half lengthwise
½ cup cane sugar
½ cup of rum
2 tablespoon unsalted butter, melted (Contains low levels of lactose)
¼ cup granulated sugar
1 cup unsalted walnut halves or pieces
1 cup Strawberries
½  cup Blueberries
½ cup Raspberries
1 lemon juice
¼ cup of cane sugar
¼ cup shaved, toasted coconut
½ cup Dehydrated pineapple, garnish
¼ cup Chocolate sprinkles, garnish
½ cup Mini dark chocolate chips, topping
Dark chocolate bar, shaved
Lactaid Vanilla Ice Cream
Lactaid Chocolate Ice Cream
Lactaid Cookies & Cream Ice Cream
¼ cup Rainbow sprinkles, garnish
1 cup Edible flowers, garnish
1 jar Maraschino cherries
½ lb Fresh cherries, with stem
1 jar Luxardo cherries

Steps:

1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.

2.  In a small bowl mix together the berries, sugar and lemon juice. Allow the mixture to sit for 20 minutes and stir occasionally allowing fruit to start to break down and release fruit juices.

3. On a lined baking sheet, mix together melted butter, sugar and walnuts. Spread evenly and bake for 8-10 minutes until sugar is melted and caramel in color, and nuts are toasted. Gently, remove the pan and allow the nuts to cool before chopping into smaller pieces for the sundae.

4. In a frying pan heat oil on medium heat. Place the bananas flat side down and brown on each side for 5 minutes. Flip the bananas and turn off the heat to add the rum.Turn the heat back on medium heat and cook the sugar and run for another 2 minutes. Turn off the heat and use a BBQ lighter to light the surface of the bananas to flambé. Once the flame stops, you can begin to build the sundae, placing the bananas down first.

Find the last 3 steps in the comments!

node.title: Take a Classic Banana Split To the Next Level

Ingredients:

Use 2 chicken breasts and garlic aioli
1⁄2 a cup of chicken stock
2 tbsp of unsalted butter
1⁄4 cup of red onion finely diced
2 celery ribs finely diced 1⁄4 cup of craisins
1tbsp of curry powder 1⁄2 tbsp of celery salt
1⁄2 tsp of freshly cracked pepper 1tsp of lemon juice to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees

2. In a shallow baking pan add chicken breasts, butter, onions, season with celery salt and

3. Add a generous amount of pepper.

4. Pour chicken stock on top and cover with foil, bake for approx. 20mins or until internal temp is 165 degrees

5. Once the chicken is done, remove it from the oven and allow it to cool.

6. Chop chicken into small dice.

7. In a medium-size bowl combine chicken, aioli, celery, craisins, curry powder, lemon juice, and additional celery salt and pepper to taste.

8. Add more or less aioli depending on preferred consistency.

9. Adjust seasoning to taste and serve with crackers or as a sandwich

Sure, we love a classic burger, but this sweet and spicy version is a work of edible art thanks to pickled onions, grilled pineapple and a homemade glaze jam-packed with flavor made using your favorite condiments from @heinz, available at @walmart. #ad #heinzartoftheburger 

Shop Now: 
https://prod-retailer.chicoryapp.com/checkout/2RJLz

Ingredients:

1 cup white vinegar
1 cup water
2 tablespoons sugar
1 tablespoon salt
1/2 red onion, thinly sliced in half moons
1 1/2 pounds ground beef
1/4 cup Heinz Ketchup
1/4 cup Heinz Honeyracha
3 tablespoons soy sauce
2 limes
2 teaspoons sesame oil
Salt and pepper
3 tablespoons canola oil, divided
4 canned pineapple rings, drained and patted dry
1/2 cup pickled jalapeños
4 tablespoons Kraft Mayonnaise
4 leaves butter lettuce
4 sweet Hawaiian bread style hamburger buns

Steps:

1. Pickled onions: In a small saucepan, combine the vinegar, water, salt, and sugar. Bring just to a simmer and cook until sugar and salt are dissolved. Place the onions in a jar or glass bowl and pour the vinegar mixture over them. Allow to cool at room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours before using.

2. Burgers: In a small bowl whisk together the Heinz Ketchup, Heinz HoneyRacha, soy sauce, lime juice and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper.

3. In a medium bowl, add the ground beef and 3 tablespoons of the ketchup mixture, and mix until combined. Form the meat into 4 patties and season with salt and pepper.

4. Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium high heat, and add 2 tablespoons of oil.

5. Place the burger patties into the skillet and cook for 4 minutes. Flip the burgers and brush with the ketchup glaze. Cook for 2 more minutes, flip, and brush with the glaze again, cooking for an additional 1-3 minutes for medium, or until desired doneness is achieved.

Find the rest of the recipe in the comments!

You got to a pool party & these are on the charcuterie board - What do you do?

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon olive oil
1 onion, finely chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 1/2 pounds russet potatoes, peeled and quartered
1 cup whole milk, divided
5 tablespoons butter, cubed
Sea salt
1 cup fresh breadcrumbs
1/2 cup fresh herbs (thyme, rosemary, parsley), chopped
Zest of 1 lemon
1/4 cup tomato paste
1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce
1 teaspoon Dijon mustard
1 large egg
1/2 cup grated carrots
1 1/3 lbs ground beef
48 slices prosciutto
Freshly grated Parmesan cheese
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven 350°F, and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

2. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.

3. Add in onion and sauté, stirring occasionally until golden, about 8 minutes.

4. Add in garlic and cook, stirring often, 2 minutes more. Remove from heat and let mixture cool slightly.

5. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium heat.

6. Add in potatoes and cook, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until completely tender. Drain well.

7. Transfer potatoes back to pot and mash until smooth.

8. Add in 3/4 cup milk and butter, and fold in with a spatula until well combined. Liberally season with salt to taste.

9. In a large bowl, mix together breadcrumbs and remaining 1/4 cup milk, and let sit 5 minutes to soften.

10. Add in onion and garlic mixture, along with herbs, lemon zest, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, egg, carrots and ground beef. Season with a large pinch of salt.

11. Place 2 slices of prosciutto in each cup of 2 standard size muffin tins, making sure to fully cover the bottom and the sides, leaving about 1/2 inch overhang on all sides.

12. Firmly press about 1/4 to 1/3 cup ground beef mixture into each prosciutto-lined mold.

13. Bake in oven 20 mins.

14. Remove meatloaves from tins and place on the prepared baking sheet.

15. Top each meatloaf with 3 tbsp mashed potatoes.

16. Grate Parmesan cheese over each meatloaf.

17. Preheat broiler to high and broil for 8 to 10 mins until tops are golden.

18. Serve immediately with roasted tomato jam or ketchup, if desired.

node.title: Finally, meatloaf you can eat on the go!

Ingredients:

3 small red potatoes, halved
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon salt
1/4 cup sliced fresh chives
1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese, plus more for sprinkling
1/2 cup cold unsalted butter
1 tablespoon butter, melted
3/4 cup buttermilk
1/4 cup unsalted butter
1/4 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon onion salt
2 cups beef broth

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.

2. Thinly slice each potato lengthwise without cutting all the way through, leaving them hinged together. Set aside.

3. In a food processor fitted with the blade attachment, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cheese and chives.

4. Add 1/2 cup butter and pulse to a coarse consistency. Add buttermilk while pulsing until the dough comes together.

5. Transfer to the cast-iron skillet, and make 6 wells around the center.

6. Gently press potato halves, flat-side down, into the wells in the biscuit dough. Brush the potatoes and biscuit top with the melted butter.

7. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the biscuit dough is golden. Cool slightly, then slice.

8. In a saucepan, heat the butter on medium. Add flour and cook until bubbling, about 2 minutes.

9. Add onion salt and beef broth and cook until thickened. Pour over slices of potato biscuits and serve.

🎥: @tastemadeuk 

Ingredients:

300g cooked macaroni
30g plain flour
30g butter
400ml whole milk
200g cheddar, grated
100g mozzarella, grated
50g parmesan, grated
1 cup yellow cornmeal
90g all-purpose flour
1 heaped tbsp caster sugar
2 tsp baking powder
Salt and freshly ground pepper
1 large egg, lightly beaten
110ml whole milk
2l veg oil for frying

Steps:

1. Melt the butter in a pan and then add the flour and stir straight away. Let this colour slightly and then start pouring in the milk a little at a time, whisking after each pour.

2. Once all added stir through all the cheeses followed by the pasta. Once all well mixed, leave to cool.

3. Divide the mixture into 8 and place onto 8 large pieces of cling film. Shape into sausages, and roll the cling film tightly around it, twisting the ends so nothing escapes. Place in the fridge to harden and cool, and then skewer. Place back in the fridge whilst you start making the batter.

4. Whisk together all the dry ingredients. Whisk the eggs and then add this to the dry ingredients along with the milk. Set aside to thicken slightly, and heat the oil to 180C.

5. Dip the mac and cheese into the batter making sure it’s completely covered. Repeat with the rest placing on a tray as you go.

6. Cook in the hot oil for a few minutes until golden all over. Repeat with the remaining mac and cheese dogs. Blot before serving.

node.text:
Nothing beets a beautifully delicious dip made with sweet beets.

🎶: roller coaster by @ohnonaliya 

Ingredients:

1 cup chickpeas, cooked
2 medium beets, boiled
1 tablespoon tahini
Juice of 1/2 lime
1 small garlic clove
Salt, to taste
3 1/3 tablespoons olive oil, divided
Pita bread
Fresh ground black pepper, to taste
Thyme leaves
1 tablespoon white sesame seeds, for garnish

Steps:

1. In a food processor, grind the chickpeas, beets, tahini, lime juice, garlic, salt and 1 tablespoon of olive oil into a paste. Set aside.

2. Cut the bread into triangles, sprinkle with olive oil, season with salt and thyme, and bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes, or until toasted.

3. Transfer hummus to a bowl, sprinkle with olive oil and garnish with sesame seeds, pepper and thyme leaves.

4. Serve with pita bread.

You don't need to turn on your oven to bake a cheesecake — just use your slow cooker!

Ingredients:

1 1/2 cup  Vanilla cookie crumbs
3 tbsp  Butter
2 tbsp  Powdered sugar
2 1/4 cup  Cream cheese
1/2 cup White sugar
2  Eggs
1 1/2  Vanilla extract
1 1/2 tsp Lemon juice
1 tbsp Cornstarch
3 tbsp Heavy cream
3/4 cups Strawberries
1/2 cup Blueberries
1/2 cup Raspberries
1/2 cup White sugar
2 tbsp Lemon juice

Steps:

1. Grease a 6-inch springform pan. Line the bottom with parchment paper and coat it lightly cooking spray. Wrap foil securely around it.

2. For the crust, mix vanilla cookie crumbs, powdered sugar and melted butter.

3. Transfer to the prepared pan and press it evenly into the bottom.

4. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and white sugar until smooth.

5. Add eggs and mix until combined.

6. In a small bowl, dissolve cornstarch with vanilla extract and lemon juice. Pour it into the cream cheese mixture.

7. Finally, incorporate the heavy cream.

8. Pour the filling into the pan on top of the crust. Gently tap the pan on a work surface to remove air bubbles.

9. Fill a 5-to 6-quart slow cooker with 1-inch hot water. Set 3 balls of aluminum foil in the center of the slow cooker.

10. Place the pan on the foil balls. Cover slow cooker with a double layer of white paper towels; place the lid securely over towels.

11. Cook until set about 1 1/2 to 2 hours on the HIGH setting. Turn off the slow cooker and let the cheesecake rest for 1 hour.

12. Carefully transfer the pan to a wire rack to cool completely. Remove foil paper from around the pan.

13. Refrigerate until chilled, at least 4 hours and preferably overnight. Carefully remove the outer ring from the pan and transfer the cake to a plate.

14. Place all ingredients in a pot on medium heat.

15. Once it starts boiling, lower the heat and simmer until the fruit becomes tender and the compote has reduced by half. Remove from heat and let cool.

16. Cover the cheesecake with the berries compote.
